🧾 PROMPT V2 (LEAN VERSION)

You are a senior full-stack engineer and UX designer.

Build a minimal floating task queue app using:

Tauri
React + Vite
TypeScript
Zustand
🎯 CORE IDEA

This is NOT a kanban board.

This is a focus task queue always visible on screen.

The goal:

user reads emails
quickly pastes tasks
always sees current + next tasks
never switches apps
🪟 WINDOW
alwaysOnTop: true
frameless
transparent
resizable
draggable
opacity control
🧠 MODES
1. FLOATING MODE (default)

Small window showing:

current task (large)
next 2–3 tasks (smaller)

DONE tasks hidden

Hover → expands window

2. FULL MODE
full task list
grouping
editing
drag reorder
📦 DATA MODEL
type Task = {
  id: string
  content: string
  completed: boolean
  groupId?: string
  order: number
  createdAt: number
}

type Group = {
  id: string
  name: string
  collapsed: boolean
}
✍️ INPUT BEHAVIOR
Enter → create new task
Paste:
split by newline
each line = new task
✅ TASK BEHAVIOR
left circle checkbox
click = mark done / undo
done tasks:
move to "Completed" section
collapsed by default
📂 GROUPS
user can create groups
tasks can belong to group
groups are collapsible
simple UI (no complexity)
🔀 DRAG & DROP
reorder tasks
move between groups
💾 STORAGE
save JSON to AppData
autosave (debounced)
load on startup
⚡ UX FEATURES
always show first active task
smooth animations
minimal UI
keyboard-first interactions
⌨️ SHORTCUTS
Enter → new task
Ctrl/Cmd + V → paste multiple tasks
Ctrl/Cmd + S → save
Ctrl/Cmd + Shift + S → toggle window
🎛 SETTINGS
opacity
window size
sticky mode toggle
🧲 SNAP BEHAVIOR
snap window to screen corners on drag
📁 OUTPUT
full working project
no placeholders
includes:
package.json
tauri config
run instructions
🚀 GOAL

App must run with:

npm install
npm run tauri dev
